theorem interior_diff_subset_interior_diff_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    interior ((A \ B) : Set X) ⊆ interior (A : Set X) \ closure (B : Set X) := by
  intro x hx
  -- `x` lies in `interior A` because `A \ B ⊆ A`.
  have hIntA : (x : X) ∈ interior (A : Set X) := by
    have h_sub : ((A \ B) : Set X) ⊆ (A : Set X) := Set.diff_subset _ _
    exact (interior_mono h_sub) hx
  -- Show that `x` is not in `closure B`.
  have hNotClB : (x : X) ∉ closure (B : Set X) := by
    intro hxCl
    -- Obtain an open neighbourhood `U` of `x` contained in `A \ B`.
    rcases (mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds).1 hx with ⟨U, hU_open, hxU, hU_sub⟩
    -- Since `x` is in the closure of `B`, this neighbourhood meets `B`.
    have h_nonempty := (mem_closure_iff.1 hxCl) U hU_open hxU
    rcases h_nonempty with ⟨y, hyU, hyB⟩
    -- But `U ⊆ A \ B`, hence `y ∉ B`, a contradiction.
    exact (hU_sub hyU).2 hyB
  exact And.intro hIntA hNotClB

theorem interior_interior_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior (interior (closure (A : Set X))) = interior (closure (A : Set X)) := by
  simpa [interior_interior]
